cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the optimization of TCP parameters for enhanced network performance in a datacenter environment. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also focuses on the comparison of home and datacenter environments, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the modification of TCP parameters based on certain criteria, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper uses simulation results to validate the performance improvement, which could also be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory).
